This paper deals with the measurement and analysis of the impact of orphan transactions on the Bitcoin network. It involves network measurements and analysis of transaction data, which suggests that orphan transactions have a significant impact on network overhead. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other possible categories include cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
